cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper deals with learning efficient representations for similarity-based search, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of neural networks for representation learning also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of hash tables for efficient search, which is a common technique in multimedia retrieval (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
